(API Authentication & Permissions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Last refresh: 2026-03-27.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This note explains how Atho secures its HTTP API, how passwords/permissions work, and why this) Tj
T*
(matters for protecting your node and funds.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Model overview) Tj
T*
(- Every API request must include:) Tj
T*
(- X-API-Key ? the token from Src/Config/Api_Keys.json) Tj
T*
(- X-User ? username associated with the key \(default atho\)) Tj
T*
(- X-Pass ? password for the user \(hashed in the key file\)) Tj
T*
(- Optional HMAC: when enabled, requests also carry X-TS and X-Sig to sign method/path/body with) Tj
T*
(a derived secret.) Tj
T*
(- Permissions are per-key; missing scopes yield 403s. Keys are stored in) Tj
T*
(Src/Config/Api_Keys.json.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Permissions) Tj
T*
(- Required scopes include:) Tj
T*
(- read ? general info endpoints) Tj
T*
(- explorer ? block/tx explorer-like data) Tj
T*
(- send_tx ? submit transactions) Tj
T*
(- mining ? mining control/status) Tj
T*
(- wallet_admin ? wallet/key mutation endpoints \(/wallet/create, /wallet/recover_mnemonic,) Tj
T*
(/wallet/import, /wallet/export, rename/delete/default\)) Tj
T*
(- node_admin ? node/config/security mutation endpoints) Tj
T*
(- Keys can have a subset; defaults are full permissions if a password is set, or read-only if no) Tj
T*
(password is provided.) Tj
T*
(- The code migrates existing keys to include required scopes on startup.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Passwords and safety) Tj
T*
(- Passwords are hashed \(SHA3-256 with a salt\) in the key file; the plain password is never) Tj
T*
(stored.) Tj
T*
(- Without X-Pass, a key cannot authorize sensitive actions even if the token is known.) Tj
T*
(- If you leave the password blank on creation, the key is restricted to read-only scopes,) Tj
T*
(reducing blast radius for non-admin usage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(HMAC \(optional but recommended when exposed\)) Tj
T*
(- If REQUIRE_HMAC is enabled, every request must include X-TS and X-Sig; the server verifies) Tj
T*
(freshness \(±60s\) and integrity over method/path/body.) Tj
T*
(- HMAC secrets are derived per key \(or you can store an explicit secret\).) Tj
T*
(- Protects against replay and tampering; use when exposing APIs beyond localhost.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(File locations) Tj
T*
(- API keys: Src/Config/Api_Keys.json) Tj
T*
(- Auto-creation: the entrypoint \(docker/docker-entrypoint.sh\) calls ensure_api_key_auto\(\) if no) Tj
T*
(keys exist; cliui/runnode call interactive setup.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters) Tj
T*
(- The API can submit transactions, manage mining, and expose node data. Without authentication,) Tj
T*
(anyone could double-spend, drain wallets, or disrupt your node.) Tj
T*
(- Strong passwords + per-key scopes + optional HMAC provide layered defense. Keep Api_Keys.json) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
