stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 760 Td
13 TL
(private \(chmod 600\) and rotate keys periodically.) Tj
T*
(- API authentication protects request authorization. Release integrity checks) Tj
T*
(\(checksums/signatures\) are a separate control layer and should be used for distributed binaries.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Operational tips) Tj
T*
(- Local dev: HMAC off, HTTPS off, bind to localhost; use strong passwords anyway.) Tj
T*
(- Exposed/production: enable HMAC, run behind TLS/reverse proxy, limit IPs via firewall, use) Tj
T*
(least-privilege keys \(separate read-only vs. send/mine\).) Tj
T*
(- Back up Api_Keys.json securely; losing it locks you out, leaking it compromises your node.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Performance behavior \(wallet endpoints\)) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/create now supports mnemonic-backed key creation parameters \(word_count,) Tj
T*
(passphrase, account, index, iterations\) and defaults to 24-word mnemonic generation.) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/recover_mnemonic recovers deterministic keys from phrase+path.) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/export exports one key bundle to .txt.) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/import imports key bundles \(.txt current format + legacy format support\).) Tj
T*
(- API boundaries normalize sender/recipient addresses to canonical HPK before send-path logic) Tj
T*
(runs.) Tj
T*
(- GET /wallet/balance uses a short in-memory cache and wallet snapshot path to reduce repeated) Tj
T*
(index scans during GUI polling.) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/balance_batch accepts multiple addresses and returns one combined response so GUI) Tj
T*
(wallet tables do one HTTP round-trip instead of N per-address calls.) Tj
T*
(- GET /wallet/history applies short TTL caching and per-request normalization memoization to) Tj
T*
(reduce repeated work during rapid refresh loops.) Tj
T*
(- GET /wallet/recent supports cursor pagination \(limit, offset, cursor\) with bounded caps to) Tj
T*
(avoid unbounded scans under load.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Network hashrate telemetry endpoints) Tj
T*
(Read-scoped endpoints now expose live and chart-ready hashrate telemetry:) Tj
T*
(- GET /network/hashrate/live) Tj
T*
(- returns current aggregate hashrate snapshot + per-reporter share) Tj
T*
(- GET /network/hashrate/chart?window_seconds=&bucket_seconds=&include_reporters=) Tj
T*
(- returns chart buckets from persisted history) Tj
T*
(- GET /network/hashrate/hourly?hours=&include_reporters=) Tj
T*
(- returns hourly historical buckets \(default 168 hours / 7 days\)) Tj
T*
(- points update hourly and include peer-shared reporter maps by default) Tj
T*
(- GET /network/hashrate/peer-shared-hourly?hours=&include_reporters=) Tj
T*
(- alias of /network/hashrate/hourly for dashboards expecting peer-shared naming) Tj
T*
(- GET /network/hashrate?window_seconds=&bucket_seconds=&include_reporters=) Tj
T*
(- combined live + chart response) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Backing files \(per network\):) Tj
T*
(- logs/<network>/network/network_hashrate_live.json) Tj
T*
(- logs/<network>/network/network_hashrate_state.json) Tj
T*
(- logs/<network>/network/network_hashrate_history.jsonl) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Network peer-count telemetry endpoint) Tj
T*
(- GET /network/node_count?active_window_seconds=&sample_limit=) Tj
T*
(- returns observed peer counts and sampled peer records from this node's view) Tj
T*
(- includes observed_counts \(known_peers, active_peers, healthy_peers, bucket stats\)) Tj
T*
(- used by the GUI Web Explorer bridge/header stats to show network-facing peer estimates) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
